<head>SOCIETY</head>
    <list type="altnames">
<item>CULTURE</item>
<item>COMMUNITY</item>
<item>CIVILIZATION</item>
<item>NATION</item>
<item>POPULATION</item>
    </list>
<div type="definition">
<p>GROUP OF HUMANS AND THE SYSTEM of ROLES AND RELATIONS BETWEEN THESE HUMANS in a DEFINITE TERRITORY.</p>
    </div>
<div type="notes">
<div type="old-chinese-criteria">
<p>1. There is no general word for human society in classical Chinese, any more than in Latin or Greek.</p>
        </div>
<div type="modern-chinese-criteria">
<p>社會 is the modern loan translation of the Western concept of society.</p>
<p>奴隸社會</p>
<p>封建社會</p>
<p>資本主義社會</p>
<p>社會主義社會</p>
<p>共產主義社會</p>
<p>rough draft to BEGIN TO identify synonym group members for analysis, based on CL etc. 18.11.2003. CH ／</p>
        </div>
